trend_summary: Images show steady suburban infill: new housing clusters, commercial roofs and a wider highway replace scattered woodland, while large green belts and golf course persist. A reservoir expands westward, but tree planting inside estates partly offsets clearing. Net effect is moderated growth, keeping medium overall density and a clear suburban setting.
notable_changes: Residential subdivisions enlarge in the central-south and north-east sectors.
Forest clearing and noticeable reservoir expansion on the western side.
Main north-south highway widened and a new cloverleaf interchange added.
Emergence of light-industrial/commercial rooftops near the south-east edge.
Incremental street-tree and park planting within established neighborhoods.
